{
  "page": "Turtle (siege engine)",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>A <b>turtle</b> is a siege engine used to protect attackers during a siege, similar to the shell of a <a href=\"/index.php/Turtle\" title=\"Turtle\">turtle</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Turtle_(siege_engine)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Storm_of_Swords\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Turtle_(siege_engine)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Storm of Swords\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>The <a href=\"/index.php/Free_folk\" title=\"Free folk\">free folk</a> use a crude turtle to attack the gates leading through the <a href=\"/index.php/Wall\" title=\"Wall\">Wall</a> at <a href=\"/index.php/Castle_Black\" title=\"Castle Black\">Castle Black</a> in the <a href=\"/index.php/Battle_beneath_the_Wall\" title=\"Battle beneath the Wall\">battle beneath the Wall</a>. It is described as a \"a hull turned upside down and opened fore and aft; a longhall on wheels\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos69.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos69.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> The turtle has a rounded top and eight huge wheels with a stout wooden frame underneath and a number of layers of raw <a href=\"/index.php/Mammoth\" title=\"Mammoth\">mammoth</a> skins on top of sheepskins and pelts. It is eventually destroyed by the men of the <a href=\"/index.php/Night%27s_Watch\" title=\"Night&#39;s Watch\">Night's Watch</a>, who drop barrels of frozen gravel on it from atop the <a href=\"/index.php/Wall\" title=\"Wall\">Wall</a>.\n</p><p>A great wooden turtle is used to protect <a href=\"/index.php/Joso%27s_Cock\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Joso&#39;s Cock\">Joso's Cock</a> during the <a href=\"/index.php/Siege_of_Meereen\" title=\"Siege of Meereen\">siege of Meereen</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos71.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos71.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> \n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Turtle_(siege_engine)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rasos69.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasos69.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords\" title=\"A Storm of Swords\">A Storm of Swords</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords-Chapter_69\" title=\"A Storm of Swords-Chapter 69\">Chapter 69</a>, Jon IX.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rasos71.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasos71.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords\" title=\"A Storm of Swords\">A Storm of Swords</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords-Chapter_71\" title=\"A Storm of Swords-Chapter 71\">Chapter 71<